<section>
  <div class="max-w-screen-lg mx-auto px-8 py-12 flex flex-col space-y-16">
    <h4 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl text-center font-bold tracking-wide">
      FAQs:
    </h4>
    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start">
      <div class="mt-2">
        <p class="text-xl md:text-xl font-bold tracking-wide">
          What is SWAP?
        </p>
        <p class="mt-1 md:mt-2 text-base md:text-lg text-gray-800">
          SWAP is a program that provides hotel/motel vouchers to literal homeless individuals/families for the duration of the severe weather. SWAP
          participants will also be provided with cold weather gear, first aid kits, hygiene kits and food when available.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start">
      <div class="mt-2">
        <p class="text-xl md:text-xl font-bold tracking-wide">
          What does SWAP consider severe weather?
        </p>
        <p class="mt-1 md:mt-2 text-base md:text-lg text-gray-800">
          During periods of inclement weather, 32 degrees Fahrenheit and wet or 20 degrees Fahrenheit and dry, SWAP will "activate,"and people experiencing homelessness can apply to receive a hotel/motel voucher at the intake location. SWAP will activate by 10:00 AM Monday through Friday. If activations occur over weekends or holidays, the intake will
          occur the prior business day.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start">
      <div class="mt-2">
        <p class="text-xl md:text-xl font-bold tracking-wide">
          What if those temperatures are not met?
        </p>
        <p class="mt-1 md:mt-2 text-base md:text-lg text-gray-800">
          If the above conditions are not met, SWAP will NOT activate and SWAP hotel/motel vouchers will NOT be available.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start">
      <div class="mt-2">
        <p class="text-xl md:text-xl font-bold tracking-wide">
          Do I qualify to receive a voucher through the SWAP program?
        </p>
        <p class="mt-1 md:mt-2 text-base md:text-lg text-gray-800">
          You qualify if you:
        </p>
        <p class="mt-1 md:mt-2 text-base md:text-lg text-gray-800">
          <ul class="mt-1 md:mt-2 text-base md:text-lg text-gray-800" >
            <li>- Live in a place not meant for daily living, (car, park, sidewalk, abandoned buildings, tent or on the street).</li>
            <li>- Are being evicted from a private dwelling unit, have no other safe place to go, and do not have the resources to obtain housing.</li>
            <li>- Will not have a safe place to sleep tonight.</li>
            <li>- Discharged from an institution, such as a mental health or substance abuse treatment facility, jail, or prison, where you were a resident for more than 30 consecutive days and you have no other safe place to go.</li>
          </ul>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start">
      <div class="mt-2">
        <p class="text-xl md:text-xl font-bold tracking-wide">
          What do I need to do to receive a voucher?
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-1 md:mt-2 text-base md:text-lg text-gray-800" >
          <li>- Intakes are held at Almost Home's Housing Navigation Center, 22 S. 4th Avenue (garden level), Brighton, CO 80601. Intakes are conducted on "activated" days between 12 and 4 pm.</li>
          <li>- To receive notifications via email, sign up here. To receive notifications via text, send an SMS to . To receive notifications via voice recording, call . Any changes in location or time of intakes will be indicated in each activation email.</li>
          <li>- All voucher recipients must perform intake, sign a waiver, and certify that they do not have a safe place to stay for the night.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

